# Contributing to Rules Documentation

## Overview

These guidelines establish the processes and standards for maintaining, updating, and contributing to our rules documentation. Following these guidelines ensures consistency and quality across all documentation.

## Related Guidelines

- [Core Principles](mdc:../domains/core/principles.mdc) - Core development principles
- [Standards](mdc:../domains/core/standards.mdc) - Code style and quality standards

## Documentation Structure

### Directory Organization

```sh
.cursor/rules/
├── INDEX.mdc                # Primary navigation and index
├── domains/                 # Domain-specific guidelines
│   ├── core/               # Core principles and standards
│   ├── frontend/           # Frontend-specific rules
│   └── tanstack/          # TanStack-specific guidelines
└── meta/                   # Documentation about documentation
    └── contributing.mdc    # This file
```

## Contribution Guidelines

### File Format

1. Frontmatter Requirements:

   ```yaml
   ---
   description: Brief description of the document's purpose
   globs: ['**/*.{ts,tsx}'] # Files this documentation applies to
   ---
   ```

2. Document Structure:

   ```markdown
   # Title

   ## Overview

   Brief introduction and purpose

   ## Related Guidelines

   Links to related documents

   ## Main Content Sections

   Organized by topic
   ```

### Writing Style

1. Technical Writing:

   - Use clear, concise language
   - Write in present tense
   - Use active voice
   - Include code examples
   - Explain why, not just what

2. Code Examples:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Show good practices
   function goodExample() {
     // Implementation
   }

   // ❌ Bad - Show anti-patterns
   function badExample() {
     // Implementation
   }
   ```

## Maintenance Procedures

### Adding New Rules

1. Planning:

   - Identify the appropriate domain
   - Review existing documentation
   - Plan the document structure
   - Consider cross-references

2. Implementation:
   - Create new .mdc file
   - Add frontmatter
   - Write content
   - Add to INDEX.mdc
   - Update related files

### Updating Existing Rules

1. Review Process:

   - Check existing content
   - Identify outdated information
   - Plan updates
   - Consider impact

2. Update Steps:
   - Update content
   - Review cross-references
   - Update INDEX.mdc if needed
   - Document changes

### Removing Rules

1. Deprecation Process:

   - Mark as deprecated
   - Update references
   - Plan removal timeline
   - Communicate changes

2. Removal Steps:
   - Remove from INDEX.mdc
   - Update cross-references
   - Archive or delete file
   - Document removal

## Quality Standards

### Documentation Requirements

1. Content Standards:

   - Clear purpose
   - Comprehensive coverage
   - Practical examples
   - Current information
   - Proper formatting

2. Technical Standards:
   - Valid markdown
   - Working links
   - Correct code examples
   - Proper indentation
   - Consistent style

### Review Process

1. Self Review:

   - Check content accuracy
   - Verify code examples
   - Test all links
   - Validate formatting
   - Spell check

2. Peer Review:
   - Technical accuracy
   - Content clarity
   - Code correctness
   - Documentation style
   - Cross-reference validity

## Version Control

### Commit Guidelines

1. Commit Messages:

   ```sh
   docs(rules): Add authentication guidelines

   - Add new authentication.mdc
   - Update INDEX.mdc with new section
   - Add cross-references in related files
   ```

2. Branch Strategy:
   - Feature: `docs/feature-name`
   - Fix: `docs/fix-description`
   - Update: `docs/update-description`

